RIYADH: The daily coronavirus cases reported in Saudi Arabia jumped to 2,585 in the past 24 hours, the health ministry said Tuesday. The daily health ministry report recorded two virus-related deaths. It also said 375 recoveries were recorded, bringing the total number of recovered cases to 543,129. In a press conference on Tuesday, Saudi Health Minister Fahd Al-Jalajel said that it is expected to record an increase in the number of coronavirus infections in the coming days. He also noted that most of the coronavirus patients who are in critical condition were ones that did not complete their vaccination doses.